\f0\fs22 \cf2 \CocoaLigature0 Of course. Based on the competitive analysis of Canvas and the technical gap analysis of the RoomPlan API, here are the key\
  areas where we can improve the iOS app.\
\
  The improvements fall into two main categories:\
   1. 
\f1\b Immediate User Experience (UX) Enhancements:
\f0\b0  Low-effort, high-impact changes to make the existing scanning process more\
      robust and user-friendly, inspired by Canvas.\
   2. 
\f1\b Major "Pro" Feature Additions:
\f0\b0  Larger development efforts that leverage untapped parts of the RoomPlan API to add\
      significant new capabilities.\
\
  \cf3 ---\cf2 \
\
  
\f1\b 1. Immediate UX Enhancements (The "Canvas" Model)
\f0\b0 \
\
  These changes focus on guiding the user to create a better scan, which in turn leads to more accurate data for our Assembly\
  Engine.\
\
   * 
\f1\b Implement a Pre-Scan Checklist:
\f0\b0 \
       * 
\f1\b What:
\f0\b0  Before the camera view opens, present a simple modal screen with a checklist for the user.\
       * 
\f1\b Guidance:
\f0\b0  "Prepare the room for the best results:\
           * [ ] Turn on all lights\
           * [ ] Open all interior doors (closets, pantries)\
           * [ ] Make sure window corners are visible\
           * [ ] Wipe your camera lens"\
       * 
\f1\b Why:
\f0\b0  This sets the user up for success before they even begin scanning, reducing the chance of errors and improving the\
         quality of the 3D model and captured images.\
\
   * 
\f1\b Add In-Scan Pattern Guidance:
\f0\b0 \
       * 
\f1\b What:
\f0\b0  During the live scan, display small, non-intrusive visual cues or animated overlays that teach the user 
\f2\i how
\f0\i0  to\
         move.\
       * 
\f1\b Guidance:
\f0\b0  Instead of just letting the user wave the phone around, we should encourage the methodical "painting" motion\
         that Canvas recommends (scan the floor, move up the wall, pan across the ceiling, move sideways, repeat).\
       * 
\f1\b Why:
\f0\b0  This actively trains the user to perform a high-quality scan. Better scan quality means more accurate measurements\
         and better image data for the Gemini service, leading directly to more reliable estimates.\
\
  \cf3 ---\cf2 \
\
  
\f1\b 2. Major "Pro" Feature Additions (RoomPlan API Gaps)
\f0\b0 \
\
  These are significant new features that would dramatically expand the app's capabilities and create a strong competitive moat.\
\
   * 
\f1\b Implement Multi-Room Scanning:
\f0\b0 \
       * 
\f1\b What:
\f0\b0  Use the \cf4 StructureBuilder\cf2  class from the RoomPlan API. This involves creating a UI flow where a user can finish\
         scanning one room and then tap an "Add Another Room" button to continue scanning adjacent spaces. The API then handles\
         merging these individual scans into a single, cohesive model of the entire floor.\
       * 
\f1\b Why:
\f0\b0  This is a "killer feature." It elevates the app from a single-room tool to a whole-home solution, making it viable\
         for general contractors, architects, and designers working on large-scale remodels. It's a clear differentiator that\
         would justify a "Pro" subscription tier.\
\
   * 
\f1\b Add Realistic 3D Asset Substitution:
\f0\b0 \
       * 
\f1\b What:
\f0\b0  Use the \cf4 RoomBuilder\cf2  API to replace the generic, colored bounding boxes that RoomPlan creates for furniture and\
         appliances with our own library of simple, generic 3D models.\
       * 
\f1\b Why:
\f0\b0  This provides a massive boost to the user's confidence and the app's perceived professionalism. When the user reviews\
          the scan and sees a recognizable (even if generic) 3D model of a sofa instead of a blue cube labeled "sofa," they will\
         have much more trust in the accuracy of the capture before they proceed to generate the estimate.\
\
